                  </persName>
             (Police-constable 252 K.) I found the property at the prisoner's father's, where I am informed he resides.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18321129-235-person2035">
                  WILLIAM 
                  GEORGE SMITH
               <interp inst="t18321129-235-person2035" type="surname" value="GEORGE SMITH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18321129-235-person2035" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18321129-235-person2035" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a biscuit-baker. I am an acquaintance of the prosecutor's, and knew the prisoner lived with him - I met him on the 28th of November, in the Minories - he saw me, and turned down John-street; I followed him through several streets, when he turned the corner, he ran, as I could perceive, by the distance he got- I at last came up to him, and said it was useless his trying to run away, as I should give him in charge - he said he would go with me; I delivered him to the officer; I said he had acted very foolishly in going on as he had - he cried, and said the only thing he had taken was a seal.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18321129-235-person2036">
                  JAMES 
                  JOHN CONNERLY
               <interp inst="t18321129-235-person2036" type="surname" value="JOHN CONNERLY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18321129-235-person2036" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18321129-235-person2036" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             (Police-constable 135 H). The prisoner was given into my charge by Mr. Smith; I made him no promise or threat, but said, "You are a very foolish young man;" he said he had taken a tea-board or two, and some other articles, which Mr. Sheffield valued at 4l., but he had got them back again.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. HEATON. Q. Will you swear you did not say it would be better for him to tell you? A. No. I did not.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18321129-235-person2037">
                  GEORGE 
                  AUGUSTUS
               <interp inst="t18321129-235-person2037" type="surname" value="AUGUSTUS"></interp>
